.
These searched among their ancestral registration, but they could not be located; therefore they were considered unclean and excluded from the priesthood. -- ezra 2:62
.
The governor said to them that they should not eat from the most holy things until a priest stood up with Urim and Thummim. -- ezra 2:63
.
The whole assembly numbered 42,360, -- ezra 2:64
.
besides their male and female servants who numbered 7,337; and they had singing men and women. -- ezra 2:65
.
